1
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:22,027
Are you looking down while watching this video? Let's dig into the shocking truth and perfect cure for text neck syndrome, a modern disease caused by smartphones.

2
00:00:22,027 --> 00:00:39,482
Anatomically, a normal adult's cervical spine is designed to maintain a gentle C-curve, or cervical lordosis. In this neutral 0-degree state, the neck supports a head weight of only about 5kg.

3
00:00:39,482 --> 00:00:56,591
However, as you tilt your head forward to look at your smartphone, the 'moment arm' lever effect lengthens, increasing the load exponentially. Even a 15-degree tilt places a 12kg load on the neck.

4
00:00:56,591 --> 00:01:12,209
If the angle increases to a 60-degree steep tilt, the load skyrockets to about 27kg. This is an immense physical shock, equivalent to carrying a 7-year-old child on the back of your neck all day.

5
00:01:12,209 --> 00:01:26,609
To withstand this immense load, the posterior neck muscles—upper trapezius, levator scapulae, and splenius—become extremely tense through constant isometric contraction to keep the head from falling.

6
00:01:26,609 --> 00:01:42,082
Conversely, the deep anterior neck flexors gradually weaken. This causes a severe biomechanical imbalance where the muscle's 'length-tension relationship' completely collapses.

7
00:01:42,082 --> 00:01:55,827
Ligaments supporting the bones also suffer from 'Creep Deformation,' a phenomenon where they lose elasticity and permanently stretch under constant mechanical stress.

8
00:01:55,827 --> 00:02:11,191
Stretched ligaments lead to the loss of the C-curve shock absorber, causing straight or text neck. This transfers the load directly to bones and discs, accelerating arthritis and degenerative lesions.

9
00:02:11,191 --> 00:02:27,318
The highly mobile C5-C6 and C6-C7 discs are especially prone to posterior herniation. The herniated disc compresses nerves, causing arm and finger numbness and muscle weakness.

10
00:02:27,318 --> 00:02:41,845
A chain reaction spreads throughout the body. Shortened pectoral muscles pull the shoulders inward, causing 'round shoulders,' and the thoracic spine curves backward into 'turtle back' kyphosis.

11
00:02:41,845 --> 00:02:58,036
Furthermore, the forward head posture disrupts the tension balance of the hyoid muscles under the jaw, pulling the mandible and becoming a hidden cause of Temporomandibular Joint Disorder (TMD).

12
00:02:58,036 --> 00:03:14,009
The hunched upper body compresses the rib cage, preventing full lung expansion. Lung capacity drops by up to 30%, plunging the body into chronic oxygen deficiency and extreme fatigue.

13
00:03:14,009 --> 00:03:31,355
Furthermore, a 2018 study in 'Nature Scientific Reports' revealed shocking structural bone changes. A bone horn called 'EOP' is growing on the occipital bone due to ligaments constantly pulling the skull.

14
00:03:31,355 --> 00:03:46,064
Regarding this bone adaptation to new environmental stimuli, scholars jokingly warn that we might be evolving into 'Smartphone Horn Sapiens,' holding phones with horns on our heads.

15
00:03:46,064 --> 00:04:04,045
To diagnose your stage, the 'Cobb's Angle' X-ray method is used. If the angle between the C2 and C7 vertebrae is less than 12.5 degrees, it is clearly diagnosed as a text neck.

16
00:04:04,045 --> 00:04:19,691
If symptoms worsen, medical treatment is essential. Abnormally locked joints and stiff soft tissues can also be released directly through physical therapy or manual therapy to restore mobility.

17
00:04:19,691 --> 00:04:32,545
Along with this, professional physical therapy using heat or ultrasound equipment is applied to relieve muscle tension and promote deep tissue blood circulation for recovery.

18
00:04:32,545 --> 00:04:49,236
For chronic myofascial lesions, Extracorporeal Shock Wave Therapy (ESWT) is highly effective. It shoots high-energy shock waves into the lesion, inducing micro-vessel formation and tissue regeneration.

19
00:04:49,236 --> 00:05:06,318
If muscle fibers form hard nodular bands (Taut Bands), a Trigger Point Injection (TPI) is administered. The needle physically breaks down the nodule to instantly relieve the muscle knot.

20
00:05:06,318 --> 00:05:21,873
Prolotherapy, injecting high-concentration dextrose, is applied to stretched and weakened posterior ligaments. It induces local inflammation, causing ligament cells to proliferate and strengthen.

21
00:05:21,873 --> 00:05:37,427
Severe pain is stabilized through nerve block injections to lower nerve thresholds. Afterward, sling exercises (Neurac) utilizing zero gravity safely rehabilitate and activate weakened deep muscles.

22
00:05:37,427 --> 00:05:54,027
However, without lifestyle correction, treatment is in vain! The Don'ts! Lying face down using your phone, or placing the monitor low and sticking your neck out like a turtle are absolute strict no-nos.

23
00:05:54,027 --> 00:06:07,945
Placing computer peripherals like a keyboard and mouse far away is also dangerous. The moment you stretch your arm to grab a distant mouse, your upper body and neck naturally hunch forward.

24
00:06:07,945 --> 00:06:21,927
Now the Dos you must practice! Align the top of your monitor exactly to your eye level, and when using a smartphone, support your elbow with the other hand and raise the device to your eye level.

25
00:06:21,927 --> 00:06:40,127
After 50 minutes of work, a 5-minute 'posture reset' is mandatory. 'Wall standing,' where you press your heels, hips, back, and back of the head flat against a wall, resets your misaligned posture.

26
00:06:40,127 --> 00:06:56,582
The core self-rehabilitation exercise you can do anywhere is the 'Chin-Tuck'. Look straight, pull your chin horizontally towards your body as if pulling the crown of your head up, strengthening the deep neck flexors.

27
00:06:56,582 --> 00:07:12,073
Next is the 'McKenzie Extension'. Open your chest wide, firmly squeeze both shoulder blades (scapulae) together in the back, and gently tilt your head backward while maintaining lumbar lordosis.

28
00:07:12,073 --> 00:07:44,691
If you've made it this far, you're already halfway there. Text neck is a condition made by bad habits, so small habits starting today can fully reverse it. But if you have arm numbness or persistent severe pain, don't endure it alone—be sure to see a specialist. Keep your screen at eye level, and stretch your neck once every fifty minutes. Remember just these two, and your neck will straighten again. Now, lift your head up and open your shoulders wide!
